---
import PortalLayout from "../layouts/PortalLayout.astro";
---

<PortalLayout title="Playbook" mainBg="#f0f9ff">
  <div class="max-w-4xl">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-2">Playbook</h1>
    <p class="text-stone-600 mb-8">Architecture, workflows, and standards for every site we build</p>

    <div class="space-y-8">

      <!-- Full Stack -->
      <section class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-red-700 mb-4">Full Stack</h2>
        <ol class="space-y-3">
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-700 font-bold shrink-0">1.</span>
            <div><strong>Astro + Tailwind CSS</strong> — pages and styling</div>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-700 font-bold shrink-0">2.</span>
            <div><strong>GitHub (<a href="https://github.com/Spirit-Media-US" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-red-700 hover:underline">Spirit-Media-US</a>)</strong> — code only, never media</div>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-700 font-bold shrink-0">3.</span>
            <div><strong>Netlify</strong> — hosting, auto-deploys on push to <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded text-xs">main</code></div>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-700 font-bold shrink-0">4.</span>
            <div><strong>Cloudflare</strong> — domain, SSL, CDN, security</div>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-700 font-bold shrink-0">5.</span>
            <div><strong>Cloudflare R2</strong> — all images, audio, video</div>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-700 font-bold shrink-0">6.</span>
            <div><strong>Sanity (<a href="https://sanity.io" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-red-700 hover:underline">sanity.io</a>)</strong> — CMS for client content editing and media management with auto-optimization</div>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-700 font-bold shrink-0">7.</span>
            <div><strong>GoHighLevel</strong> — CRM &amp; forms for internal sites, tagged by ministry</div>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-700 font-bold shrink-0">8.</span>
            <div><strong>Claude (<a href="https://claude.ai" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-red-700 hover:underline">claude.ai</a>)</strong> — conversational updates and builds</div>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-700 font-bold shrink-0">9.</span>
            <div><strong>UptimeRobot</strong> — uptime monitoring (every 5 min, all sites)</div>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </section>

      <!-- SMP Build Protocol -->
      <section class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-red-700 mb-1">The SMP Build Protocol</h2>
        <p class="text-stone-500 text-sm mb-1">Internal name: <strong>SMP Build Protocol</strong> &nbsp;·&nbsp; Client-facing name: <strong>The Transformation System</strong></p>
        <p class="text-stone-600 text-sm mb-5">Eight phases with one mandatory Audit Gate. Every site migration follows this map — no exceptions. The Audit Gate is Phase 4.5 and is non-negotiable.</p>

        <div class="space-y-4">

          <div class="flex gap-3">
            <div class="shrink-0 w-7 h-7 rounded-full bg-red-700 text-white text-xs font-bold flex items-center justify-center">1</div>
            <div>
              <p class="font-semibold text-stone-800 text-sm">Infrastructure</p>
              <p class="text-stone-500 text-xs">GitHub repo, Netlify site, Sanity project, Cloudflare domain, R2 bucket — all wired together via API. <strong class="text-stone-700">Create <code class="bg-white px-1 rounded">CLAUDE.md</code> in repo root before any other work begins.</strong></p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex gap-3">
            <div class="shrink-0 w-7 h-7 rounded-full bg-red-700 text-white text-xs font-bold flex items-center justify-center">2</div>
            <div>
              <p class="font-semibold text-stone-800 text-sm">Structure</p>
              <p class="text-stone-500 text-xs">Initialize Astro + Tailwind. Create all pages, nav, and footer. Set typography foundation before writing any CSS.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex gap-3">
            <div class="shrink-0 w-7 h-7 rounded-full bg-red-700 text-white text-xs font-bold flex items-center justify-center">3</div>
            <div>
              <p class="font-semibold text-stone-800 text-sm">Design &amp; Content</p>
              <p class="text-stone-500 text-xs">Add all copy. Upload media to R2 or Sanity. Add SEO meta per page. Refine design and UX.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex gap-3">
            <div class="shrink-0 w-7 h-7 rounded-full bg-red-700 text-white text-xs font-bold flex items-center justify-center">4</div>
            <div>
              <p class="font-semibold text-stone-800 text-sm">Sanity CMS Wiring</p>
              <p class="text-stone-500 text-xs">Define schemas. Migrate content into Sanity documents. Wire Astro pages to Sanity. Deploy schema to cloud. Set up Sanity → Netlify deploy webhook.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Audit Gate -->
          <div class="border border-red-200 bg-red-50 rounded-lg p-4 my-2">
            <p class="font-bold text-red-700 text-sm mb-3">⛔ Phase 4.5 — Audit Gate (mandatory)</p>
            <p class="text-stone-600 text-xs mb-3">Run all three scans before proceeding to Phase 5. Fix every finding before moving on. The Audit Gate is what separates a disciplined migration from a broken one.</p>
            <div class="space-y-3">
              <div>
                <p class="font-semibold text-stone-700 text-xs mb-1">Scan A — Migration Fidelity</p>
                <p class="text-stone-500 text-xs">Fetch the original live site and compare nav structure, page count, CTAs, and key content against the new build. Document what was already delivered and what is missing.</p>
              </div>
              <div>
                <p class="font-semibold text-stone-700 text-xs mb-1">Scan B — Typography Match</p>
                <p class="text-stone-500 text-xs">Extract the live site's exact fonts and colors from its CSS. Wire them directly into <code class="bg-white px-1 rounded">global.css</code> before writing any Astro styles. Never design from scratch — match the client's existing brand first.</p>
              </div>
              <div>
                <p class="font-semibold text-stone-700 text-xs mb-1">Scan C — Design Integrity</p>
                <p class="text-stone-500 text-xs">Grep all pages for hardcoded hex values, inline styles, and font overrides that violate the design system. Every hit is a violation — fix before proceeding.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="pt-2 border-t border-red-200">
                <p class="font-semibold text-stone-700 text-xs mb-1">Output of Audit Gate</p>
                <p class="text-stone-500 text-xs">Google Doc: "[Site Name] — Transformation Layer Report" — Part One (Already Delivered) and Part Two (Recommended Improvements). Delivered to Kevin for client review before Phase 5.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex gap-3">
            <div class="shrink-0 w-7 h-7 rounded-full bg-red-700 text-white text-xs font-bold flex items-center justify-center">5</div>
            <div>
              <p class="font-semibold text-stone-800 text-sm">CAR / Transformation Layer</p>
              <p class="text-stone-500 text-xs">Deliver Transformation Layer Report to Kevin for client review. Kevin and client decide which Recommended Improvements to implement before launch. Implement approved improvements.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex gap-3">
            <div class="shrink-0 w-7 h-7 rounded-full bg-red-700 text-white text-xs font-bold flex items-center justify-center">6</div>
            <div>
              <p class="font-semibold text-stone-800 text-sm">Design Polish &amp; QA</p>
              <p class="text-stone-500 text-xs">Run all 8 automated QA scans (build check, hardcoded colors, alt text, SEO meta, broken links, dev URLs, placeholder content, sitemap). Fix every finding. Then human review on mobile and desktop.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex gap-3">
            <div class="shrink-0 w-7 h-7 rounded-full bg-red-700 text-white text-xs font-bold flex items-center justify-center">7</div>
            <div>
              <p class="font-semibold text-stone-800 text-sm">Launch</p>
              <p class="text-stone-500 text-xs">Connect custom domain. Confirm SSL. Submit sitemap to Google Search Console. Set up UptimeRobot. Enable analytics. Invite client to Sanity Studio. Send Client Guide.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex gap-3">
            <div class="shrink-0 w-7 h-7 rounded-full bg-red-700 text-white text-xs font-bold flex items-center justify-center">8</div>
            <div>
              <p class="font-semibold text-stone-800 text-sm">Client Delivery</p>
              <p class="text-stone-500 text-xs mb-2">Send client email with: live URL, Sanity Studio link, Client Guide link, and support contact.</p>
              <p class="text-stone-500 text-xs mb-1 font-semibold">Email template:</p>
              <div class="relative">
                <div class="bg-stone-100 px-3 py-2 rounded text-xs text-stone-600 whitespace-pre-wrap leading-relaxed" id="delivery-email">Subject: Your website is live! — [Site Name]

Hi [Client Name],

Your new website is live at [domain]!

We've put together a guide to help you manage your site content on your own:
→ https://portal.spiritmediapublishing.com/clients

To set up your team's content editing access, please reply with the name and email address for each person who should be able to edit. We'll send them a Sanity Studio invite with everything they need to get started.

For anything beyond content edits — new pages, design changes, forms, or technical work — just email us at hello@spiritmediapublishing.com.

Welcome aboard!
SMP Team</div>
                <button class="copy-btn absolute top-2 right-2 px-3 py-1 bg-red-50 hover:bg-red-100 text-red-700 rounded text-xs font-semibold font-sans" data-copy-target="delivery-email">Copy</button>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

        </div>

        <!-- Design Library link -->
        <div class="mt-6 pt-5 border-t border-stone-200">
          <p class="text-stone-600 text-sm mb-2">Use the <a href="/design-library" class="text-red-700 hover:underline font-semibold">Design Library →</a> to browse all 7 style packages and 21 color palettes. When starting a new site, select a package and tell Claude which one to use.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Tools integration -->
        <div class="mt-4 pt-4 border-t border-stone-200">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-stone-800 mb-3">How the Tools Page Automates This</h3>
          <p class="text-stone-500 text-xs mb-3">Three tools on the <a href="/templates" class="text-red-700 hover:underline">Templates page</a> cover the first three decision points in the protocol:</p>
          <div class="space-y-2">
            <div class="flex gap-3 bg-stone-50 border border-stone-200 rounded p-3">
              <div class="shrink-0 text-red-700 font-bold text-sm">Step 1</div>
              <div>
                <p class="font-semibold text-stone-700 text-xs">Website Migration Proposal</p>
                <p class="text-stone-500 text-xs">Enter the client's URL. Auto-generates a Google Doc proposal and complexity report with bottom/mid/top pricing. No manual inputs — the tool reads the site and builds the deliverable.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="flex gap-3 bg-stone-50 border border-stone-200 rounded p-3">
              <div class="shrink-0 text-red-700 font-bold text-sm">Step 2</div>
              <div>
                <p class="font-semibold text-stone-700 text-xs">Initiate Build (Phase 1)</p>
                <p class="text-stone-500 text-xs">After the proposal is accepted, select the project from the dropdown. One click scaffolds all infrastructure: GitHub repo, Sanity project, Netlify site, deploy key, and webhook — entirely via API.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="flex gap-3 bg-stone-50 border border-stone-200 rounded p-3">
              <div class="shrink-0 text-red-700 font-bold text-sm">Step 3</div>
              <div>
                <p class="font-semibold text-stone-700 text-xs">Pre-Launch QA (Phase 6)</p>
                <p class="text-stone-500 text-xs">After the build is complete, run the automated QA suite. Scans the site repo for hardcoded colors, missing alt text, broken links, placeholder content, and more. Returns findings by category before human review begins.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Media -->
      <section class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-red-700 mb-2">Media</h2>
        <p class="text-stone-600 text-sm mb-4">Media never goes in GitHub. All repos block this via .gitignore.</p>
        <div class="space-y-2 text-stone-600 text-sm mb-4">
          <p><strong>Images:</strong> Managed through <strong>Sanity</strong> — clients upload directly in Sanity Studio. Auto-optimized and served via Sanity CDN. No SMP involvement needed.</p>
          <p><strong>Audio:</strong> Stored in <strong>Cloudflare R2</strong> — Kevin uploads manually.</p>
          <p><strong>Video:</strong> Hosted on <strong>YouTube</strong> and embedded on site (adds SEO value). R2 as backup when YouTube isn't appropriate.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded p-3 text-sm text-amber-800 mb-4">
          ⚠️ <strong>Never rename or delete a live R2 file</strong> — it will break every page that references it. (Sanity handles its own references safely.)
        </div>

        <h3 class="font-bold text-stone-800 mb-2">R2 Bucket &amp; Custom Domain</h3>
        <p class="text-stone-600 text-sm mb-2">One bucket organized by site, served from a clean subdomain:</p>
        <div class="bg-stone-100 px-4 py-2 rounded font-mono text-xs text-stone-600 mb-2">assets.spiritmediapublishing.com</div>
        <div class="bg-stone-100 px-4 py-3 rounded font-mono text-xs text-stone-600 mb-4 whitespace-pre leading-relaxed">spirit-media-assets/
├── spirit-media-publishing/  (videos, audio, pdfs)
├── fathers-heart-bible/      (audio, videos)
├── work-on-yourself/         (audio)
└── believers-library/        (videos)</div>
        <p class="text-stone-500 text-xs mb-4">Shared assets (logos used across sites) go in <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded">spirit-media-publishing/</code>. Name files lowercase with hyphens: <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded">genesis-chapter-1-audio.mp3</code></p>

        <h3 class="font-bold text-stone-800 mb-2">How to add media to R2 (audio/video)</h3>
        <ol class="space-y-1 text-stone-600 text-sm">
          <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-red-700 font-bold shrink-0">1.</span> Client shares Google Drive folder with Kevin</li>
          <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-red-700 font-bold shrink-0">2.</span> Kevin downloads and organizes files</li>
          <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-red-700 font-bold shrink-0">3.</span> Upload to the correct site folder in R2 at <a href="https://dash.cloudflare.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-red-700 hover:underline">dash.cloudflare.com</a></li>
          <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-red-700 font-bold shrink-0">4.</span> File is live immediately at <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded text-xs">assets.spiritmediapublishing.com/[site]/[file]</code></li>
          <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-red-700 font-bold shrink-0">5.</span> Kevin updates site code to point to the new R2 URL</li>
        </ol>
        <p class="text-stone-500 text-xs mt-3">For images, clients upload directly in Sanity Studio — no R2 or SMP involvement needed.</p>
      </section>

      <!-- Forms & GHL -->
      <section class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-red-700 mb-2">Forms &amp; GoHighLevel</h2>
        <p class="text-stone-600 text-sm mb-4">For Spirit Media internal sites, contact forms route to our GoHighLevel CRM, tagged by site. For client sites, forms may use Netlify Forms or another provider depending on the project.</p>

        <h3 class="font-bold text-stone-800 mb-2">GHL Tagging Strategy (Internal Sites)</h3>
        <p class="text-stone-500 text-sm mb-2">Every internal form applies a source tag so contacts can be segmented by ministry:</p>
        <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-4">
          <table class="w-full text-sm text-left border border-stone-200 rounded">
            <thead class="bg-stone-100">
              <tr>
                <th class="px-3 py-2 text-stone-700 font-semibold">Form / Entry Point</th>
                <th class="px-3 py-2 text-stone-700 font-semibold">GHL Tag</th>
                <th class="px-3 py-2 text-stone-700 font-semibold">Pipeline</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody class="text-stone-600">
              <tr class="border-t border-stone-100"><td class="px-3 py-2">SMP general contact</td><td class="px-3 py-2"><code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded text-xs">source:smp</code></td><td class="px-3 py-2">General Inquiry</td></tr>
              <tr class="border-t border-stone-100"><td class="px-3 py-2">Father's Heart Bible</td><td class="px-3 py-2"><code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded text-xs">source:fhb</code></td><td class="px-3 py-2">FHB Waitlist</td></tr>
              <tr class="border-t border-stone-100"><td class="px-3 py-2">Work On Yourself coaching</td><td class="px-3 py-2"><code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded text-xs">source:woy</code></td><td class="px-3 py-2">Coaching</td></tr>
              <tr class="border-t border-stone-100"><td class="px-3 py-2">Believer's Library waitlist</td><td class="px-3 py-2"><code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded text-xs">source:believers-library</code></td><td class="px-3 py-2">App Launch</td></tr>
              <tr class="border-t border-stone-100"><td class="px-3 py-2">Kingdom Messenger signup</td><td class="px-3 py-2"><code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded text-xs">source:kingdom-messenger</code></td><td class="px-3 py-2">Newsletter</td></tr>
              <tr class="border-t border-stone-100"><td class="px-3 py-2">Prayer request forms</td><td class="px-3 py-2"><code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded text-xs">source:prayer</code></td><td class="px-3 py-2">Pastoral Care</td></tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <h3 class="font-bold text-stone-800 mb-2">Embedding a GHL Form in Astro</h3>
        <div class="bg-stone-100 px-4 py-3 rounded font-mono text-xs text-stone-600 whitespace-pre leading-relaxed">&lt;!-- In your .astro file --&gt;
&lt;div class="ghl-form-wrapper"&gt;
  &lt;!-- Paste GHL embed code here --&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;</div>
        <p class="text-stone-500 text-xs mt-2">Request embed codes from Kevin. He creates forms in GHL with proper tags and pipelines.</p>
      </section>

      <!-- Team Prompt -->
      <section class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-red-700 mb-2">Team Prompt</h2>
        <p class="text-stone-500 text-sm mb-3">Paste at the top of every new Claude chat to give full project context.</p>
        <div class="relative">
          <div class="bg-stone-100 border border-stone-200 rounded p-4 font-mono text-xs text-stone-700 whitespace-pre-wrap leading-relaxed" id="team-prompt">You are helping Spirit Media Publishing build and maintain websites. Stack: Astro + Tailwind CSS. GitHub org: Spirit-Media-US (all repos public). Hosting: Netlify, Spirit Media team, build = npm run build, publish = dist. DNS/SSL/CDN: Cloudflare, proxy active. Media: Sanity (sanity.io) for images on media-heavy sites — auto-optimizes and serves via CDN. Cloudflare R2 for audio. Video goes on YouTube and is embedded on site. R2 is backup for video when YouTube isn't appropriate. Never put media in GitHub, all repos block this via .gitignore. Forms: GoHighLevel, all contacts tagged by site.

This site: [site name] | Repo: github.com/Spirit-Media-US/[repo-name] | Domain: [domain] | R2 bucket: [bucket-name or n/a]

Rules: Never push without local preview first (npm run dev). All work goes to the dev branch — never push directly to main. Only merge dev to main when Kevin says "push to main." Pricing off all public pages. All contacts to GHL. Media always to R2 or Sanity.

Today's task: [describe what you need]</div>
          <button id="copy-prompt-btn" class="mt-3 px-4 py-2 bg-red-50 border border-stone-200 hover:bg-white hover:border-red-700 text-red-700 text-xs font-semibold rounded transition-colors">Copy Prompt</button>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Development Infrastructure -->
      <section class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-red-700 mb-4">Development Infrastructure</h2>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-stone-700 mb-2">Bethel (Dev Server)</h3>
            <div class="bg-stone-100 px-4 py-2 rounded font-mono text-sm text-stone-700 mb-1">ssh bethel</div>
            <p class="text-stone-500 text-sm">Hetzner CCX33 — Ubuntu 22.04, Tailscale IP <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded">100.114.220.65</code>, all project repos at <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded">/home/deploy/Sites/</code></p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-stone-700 mb-2">Code Server (VS Code in browser)</h3>
            <a href="https://dev.spiritmediapublishing.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-red-700 hover:underline text-sm font-mono">dev.spiritmediapublishing.com</a>
            <p class="text-stone-500 text-sm mt-1">Requires Tailscale VPN. Full IDE access to all repos.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-stone-700 mb-2">Tailscale VPN</h3>
            <div class="bg-stone-100 px-4 py-2 rounded font-mono text-sm text-stone-700">100.114.220.65</div>
            <p class="text-stone-500 text-sm mt-1">Required for SSH and code-server access</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Deployment Workflow -->
      <section class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-red-700 mb-4">Deployment Workflow</h2>
        <p class="text-stone-500 text-sm mb-4">All work happens on <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded">dev</code>. Only merge to <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded">main</code> when ready to publish. Each push to main = one Netlify build credit. Free plan includes <strong>1,000 build credits/month</strong> (~2–3 min per build = ~300 pushes/month). Batch all changes before merging.</p>
        <div class="space-y-3">
          <div class="bg-stone-50 border-l-4 border-red-700 px-4 py-3 rounded-r">
            <p class="font-semibold text-stone-700 text-sm mb-1">1. Switch to dev</p>
            <code class="text-xs text-stone-600">git checkout dev</code>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-stone-50 border-l-4 border-red-700 px-4 py-3 rounded-r">
            <p class="font-semibold text-stone-700 text-sm mb-1">2. Preview locally</p>
            <code class="text-xs text-stone-600">npm run dev</code>
            <p class="text-stone-500 text-xs mt-1">localhost:4321 — never push without previewing first</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-stone-50 border-l-4 border-red-700 px-4 py-3 rounded-r">
            <p class="font-semibold text-stone-700 text-sm mb-1">3. Commit and push to dev</p>
            <code class="text-xs text-stone-600">git add . && git commit --no-verify -m "message" && git push origin dev</code>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-stone-50 border-l-4 border-red-700 px-4 py-3 rounded-r">
            <p class="font-semibold text-stone-700 text-sm mb-1">4. Merge to main to publish</p>
            <code class="text-xs text-stone-600">git checkout main && git merge dev && git push origin main && git checkout dev</code>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Deploy Troubleshooting -->
      <section class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-red-700 mb-4">Deploy Troubleshooting</h2>
        <p class="text-stone-600 text-sm mb-4">When a Netlify build fails, check the deploy log at <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded text-xs">app.netlify.com → Deploys → failed deploy → Deploy log</code>. Common errors:</p>
        <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-4">
          <table class="w-full text-sm text-left border border-stone-200 rounded">
            <thead class="bg-stone-100">
              <tr>
                <th class="px-3 py-2 text-stone-700 font-semibold">Error</th>
                <th class="px-3 py-2 text-stone-700 font-semibold">Cause</th>
                <th class="px-3 py-2 text-stone-700 font-semibold">Fix</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody class="text-stone-600">
              <tr class="border-t border-stone-100"><td class="px-3 py-2 font-mono text-xs">Cannot find module</td><td class="px-3 py-2">Missing dependency</td><td class="px-3 py-2"><code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded text-xs">npm install</code> and commit <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded text-xs">package-lock.json</code></td></tr>
              <tr class="border-t border-stone-100"><td class="px-3 py-2 font-mono text-xs">Build exceeded memory</td><td class="px-3 py-2">Too many large images or files in build</td><td class="px-3 py-2">Move media to R2, not <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded text-xs">public/</code></td></tr>
              <tr class="border-t border-stone-100"><td class="px-3 py-2 font-mono text-xs">AstroError</td><td class="px-3 py-2">Syntax or component error</td><td class="px-3 py-2">Run <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded text-xs">npm run build</code> locally first — fix before pushing</td></tr>
              <tr class="border-t border-stone-100"><td class="px-3 py-2 font-mono text-xs">404 after deploy</td><td class="px-3 py-2">Publish dir wrong or page not generated</td><td class="px-3 py-2">Confirm publish dir is <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded text-xs">dist</code> in Netlify settings</td></tr>
              <tr class="border-t border-stone-100"><td class="px-3 py-2 font-mono text-xs">DNS_PROBE_FINISHED</td><td class="px-3 py-2">Cloudflare DNS misconfigured</td><td class="px-3 py-2">Verify CNAME points to Netlify and proxy is orange</td></tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-stone-50 border border-stone-200 rounded p-3 text-sm text-stone-600">
          💡 <strong>Reading Netlify logs:</strong> Scroll to the bottom of the deploy log first — the final error message is usually the root cause. Everything above it is normal build output.
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- If Something Goes Wrong -->
      <section class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-red-700 mb-4">If Something Goes Wrong</h2>
        <p class="text-stone-600 text-sm mb-4">Don't panic — but do act quickly and communicate.</p>
        <div class="space-y-3">
          <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded p-3 text-sm text-amber-800">
            <strong>Site looks broken after your push</strong> — Tell Kevin immediately with a description of what you changed.
          </div>
          <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded p-3 text-sm text-amber-800">
            <strong>Merge conflict</strong> — Don't force push. Stop and message Kevin immediately.
          </div>
          <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded p-3 text-sm text-amber-800">
            <strong>Netlify build failed</strong> — Check the Netlify dashboard and share the error log with Kevin.
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Best Practices -->
      <section class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-red-700 mb-4">Best Practices</h2>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-stone-700 text-sm">
          <li>✓ Always preview before pushing: <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded">npm run dev</code></li>
          <li>✓ Always build before merging to main: <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded">npm run build</code></li>
          <li>✓ Never commit media files to Git</li>
          <li>✓ Never rename or delete a live media file</li>
          <li>✓ One push to main per session — batch all changes first</li>
          <li>✓ Pricing off all public pages</li>
          <li>✓ Internal site forms route to GHL, tagged by site</li>
          <li>✓ Keep .env files in <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded">/home/deploy/bin/</code></li>
          <li>✓ Use meaningful commit messages</li>
          <li>✓ Kevin approves all merges to main</li>
          <li>✓ Before pushing any fix, verify it doesn't break something else — check affected pages on mobile and desktop</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <!-- Uptime Monitoring -->
      <section class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-red-700 mb-4">Uptime Monitoring</h2>
        <p class="text-stone-600 text-sm mb-4">UptimeRobot checks every site every 5 minutes and sends email alerts if anything goes down. Every SMP site gets added to UptimeRobot as part of the launch checklist.</p>
        <a href="https://uptimerobot.com/dashboard" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="inline-block px-4 py-2 bg-red-50 border border-stone-200 hover:bg-white hover:border-red-700 text-red-700 text-sm font-semibold rounded transition-colors mb-4">Open UptimeRobot Dashboard →</a>

        <h3 class="font-bold text-stone-800 mb-2">Downtime Response</h3>
        <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded p-3 text-sm text-amber-800">
          <strong>If you receive a downtime alert:</strong> Do not push a new build. First check if the issue resolves on its own within 2 minutes (Netlify occasionally has brief hiccups). If the site is still down after 5 minutes, contact Kevin immediately.
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Need Help? -->
      <section class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-red-700 mb-4">Need Help?</h2>
        <p class="text-stone-600 text-sm mb-4">Route questions to the right person:</p>
        <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-6">
          <table class="w-full text-sm text-left border border-stone-200 rounded">
            <thead class="bg-stone-100">
              <tr>
                <th class="px-3 py-2 text-stone-700 font-semibold">Problem</th>
                <th class="px-3 py-2 text-stone-700 font-semibold">Contact</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody class="text-stone-600">
              <tr class="border-t border-stone-100"><td class="px-3 py-2">Build failures, Git conflicts, server access</td><td class="px-3 py-2 font-semibold">Kevin</td></tr>
              <tr class="border-t border-stone-100"><td class="px-3 py-2">Content updates, copy changes</td><td class="px-3 py-2 font-semibold">Kevin</td></tr>
              <tr class="border-t border-stone-100"><td class="px-3 py-2">Design decisions, domain/DNS, Netlify, merge approvals</td><td class="px-3 py-2 font-semibold">Kevin</td></tr>
              <tr class="border-t border-stone-100"><td class="px-3 py-2">GHL forms, CRM, marketing automation</td><td class="px-3 py-2 font-semibold">Kevin</td></tr>
              <tr class="border-t border-stone-100"><td class="px-3 py-2">Client requests</td><td class="px-3 py-2 font-semibold">Kevin</td></tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <h3 class="font-bold text-stone-800 mb-2">Resources</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-stone-600 text-sm">
          <li><a href="https://docs.astro.build" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-red-700 hover:underline">→ Astro Documentation</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://www.sanity.io/docs" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-red-700 hover:underline">→ Sanity Documentation</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://tailwindcss.com/docs" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-red-700 hover:underline">→ Tailwind CSS Documentation</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://docs.netlify.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-red-700 hover:underline">→ Netlify Documentation</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://dash.cloudflare.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-red-700 hover:underline">→ Cloudflare Dashboard</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://github.com/Spirit-Media-US" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-red-700 hover:underline">→ Spirit-Media-US GitHub</a></li>
        </ul>
      </section>

    </div>
  </div>
</PortalLayout>

<script>
  document.getElementById('copy-prompt-btn')?.addEventListener('click', function() {
    const text = document.getElementById('team-prompt')?.textContent || '';
    navigator.clipboard.writeText(text).then(() => {
      this.textContent = 'Copied!';
      setTimeout(() => { this.textContent = 'Copy Prompt'; }, 2000);
    });
  });
  document.querySelectorAll('.copy-btn[data-copy-target]').forEach((btn) => {
    btn.addEventListener('click', function() {
      const targetId = this.getAttribute('data-copy-target');
      const text = document.getElementById(targetId)?.textContent || '';
      navigator.clipboard.writeText(text).then(() => {
        const originalText = this.textContent;
        this.textContent = 'Copied!';
        setTimeout(() => { this.textContent = originalText; }, 2000);
      });
    });
  });
</script>
